==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Monocrotism
<hw>Mo*noc"ro*tism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>mo`nos</grk> alone + <?/ a beating.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>That condition of the pulse in which the pulse curve or sphygmogram
shows but a single crest, the dicrotic elevation entirely
disappearing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Monocular</ent>⟦br⟧
